ca.cgjennings.ui

Interface JWebPanel.PopupHandler

  • Enclosing class:
    JWebPanel

    public static interface JWebPanel.PopupHandler
    A callback that can be set on the panel to add support for pop-up windows. To implement support, you set an implementation of this class as the popup handler for the pane. When a popup is requested by a Web page, your handler will be called. Note that this call is not done on the event dispatch thread. If your handler returns anything other than null or false, the popup will be allowed. A new JWebPanel will be created for you to contain the popup. You must be listening for a change to the JWebPanel.POPUP_PANEL_PROPERTY from the panel Web panel. The old value of this property will be whatever non-null object you returned from allowPopup(ca.cgjennings.ui.JWebPanel.PopupProperties). The new value of the property will be the new JWebPanel that must serve as the basis for displaying the pop-up.

    • Method Detail

      • allowPopup

        Object allowPopup(JWebPanel.PopupProperties properties)
        Returns a non-null object if the panel should allow a pop-up window. The user of the Web panel must respond to the JWebPanel.POPUP_PANEL_PROPERTY property change to complete the process and display the pop-up. The value returned by the handler will be sent to the property change listener as the old value of the property. This allows the listener to keep track of which new Web panel belongs to which pop-up request.
        Parameters:
        properties - the properties requested for the new pop-up window
        Returns:
        null or Boolean.FALSE to deny the pop-up; any other value to allow it
